Text.Value: Do you have any unfinished business?
Do you have any advice for me?
Leave.
'Transforming'? 'Glimmering'? What do you mean?
Transforming... glimmering...

Text.Value: To be heard...
What is it like to die?
What was your greatest desire in life?
Use your voice... always...
Do you have anything of value?
The story... never told. The passing... beautiful...

Text.Value: Who is the Absolute?
What were you doing here?
Manuscript. Story of... goblins... Absolute. Don't know... how it ends...
Volothamp... Geddarm. My mother's... son...
*The corpse does not stir. It will answer no more questions.*
*The corpse regards you lifelessly.*
Who are you?
Investigating... the Absolute. Goblins'... new god...
*The spell's power wanes. You can ask no more questions.*
Quick mind... silver tongue...
*The corpse seems willing to speak - but not to its killer.*
Unreal god... unheard of... spread like a plague...

Synopsis: In this dialogue, Volo has died and is a lifeless corpse. Rather than his usual jocular self, he's a shade who can hardly speak.
